    "encounter_brief": "(U) BLUF \u2014 The UAS contact is identified as a DJI Mavic 3 conducting reconnaissance with moderate confidence; recommend a non-kinetic directional RF jam to push the UAS off-site.\n\n(U) MULTI-SENSOR FUSION\n  \u00b7 RF \u2014 fast FHSS (likely OcuSync / proprietary FHSS), p(uas) 0.454\n  \u00b7 Thermal IR \u2014 1 blob detected, likely UAS, p(uas) 0.5\n  \u00b7 Visual EO \u2014 1 drone silhouette, quad silhouette in the sky, p(uas) 0.48\n  \u00b7 Fused confidence \u2014 0.434 \u00b7 sensors contributing \u2014 [RF, thermal, visual]\n\n(U) THREAT ASSESSMENT \u2014 The intent of the UAS is assessed as reconnaissance, likely gathering information on the Camp Pendleton perimeter. This poses a potential security risk to the installation, necessitating a timely response.\n\n(U) ENGAGEMENT OPTIONS (top 3 from the ROE ladder)\n  - [NON-KINETIC] Directional RF jam \u2014 authority: Installation Commander (delegable to OIC EW)\n  - [NON-KINETIC] GPS spoof (push UAS off course) \u2014 authority: Installation Commander + EW spectrum auth\n  - [PASSIVE] Track + log only (SkyTracker-style passive ID) \u2014 authority: Watch officer\n\n(U) RECOMMENDED COA \u2014 Directional RF jam \u2014 authority: Installation Commander (delegable to OIC EW) \u2014 this option effectively disrupts the UAS's operation and pushes it off-site, mitigating the reconnaissance threat.\n\n(U) AUTHORITIES \u2014 10 USC 130i (UAS authorities), DoDD 3000.09, JCO-CUAS Operational Concept."
  },
